summary: I remember I once owned a game guide for Pokemon Yellow. I think it was an unofficial guide, maybe from Prima? But anyways, it...
body:
I remember I once owned a game guide for Pokemon Yellow. I think it was an unofficial guide, maybe from Prima?

But anyways, it had some really cool things in it, like a few glitches and exploits you could find, and it’s a shame that I don’t seem to have it anymore. 

In the back, there was a list of recommended teams to use when battling against friends. And most of it was pretty much copy and paste. Lots of technical stuff about using Arcanine because of its speed, Butterfree for status effects, Parasects to counter Mewtwo, Mewtwo itself…

But there was one of these selected teams that really stood out. It was a team which included Pokemon like Magikarp, Metapod, Chansey…

I forget which was supposed to be the last one, but it doesn’t really matter. Apparently, you were supposed to say something implying that you had a really good Pokemon which would make up for five jokes, and just as you sent out your last Pokemon, you were to pop out your friend’s batteries without them seeing, and bemoan the fact that they never got to see you take out their Mewtwo with the last of your Pokemon.
